'''Daniel Logan''' (born [[June 6]], [[1987]])<ref name="Website" /> is a [[Wikipedia:New Zealand|New Zealand]]&ndash;born actor who played [[Boba Fett]] in [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']] and ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'', and [[Mox]] in ''[[Star Wars: The Bad Batch]]''.

==Biography==
[[File:Daniel_Logan.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Daniel Logan, circa [[2000]]]]
Before filmmakers offered Daniel Logan the role of young [[Boba Fett]] in [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']], they offered the part to an 11-year-old [[Wikipedia:New Zealand|New Zealand]] boy, Tupoutahi Winitana—[[Bodie Taylor]]'s co-performer in the Māori stage production ''Ahorangi 2000''. Due to the significance of Winitana's role in ''Ahorangi 2000'' and scheduling conflicts between the stage performance and filming, Tupoutahi was forced to turn down the ''Star Wars'' role.<ref name="NZHerald">{{WebCite|url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/lifestyle/young-actor-says-no-to-skywalking/VCU72YRZKZDEUVC5WA6R7R45AQ|text=Young actor says no to Skywalking|author=Louisa Cleave|date=2000-07-07|work=[[Wikipedia:The New Zealand Herald|''The New Zealand Herald'']]|archivedate=20210307123528}}</ref> 

For his role in ''Attack of the Clones'', [[George Lucas]] allowed Logan to give his own interpretation of the character<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2007/02/24/nycc-07-star-wars-behind-the-mask|text=NYCC 07: Star Wars &ndash;&ndash; Behind The Mask|author=Steven Horn|date=2007-02-23|work=[[Wikipedia:IGN|''IGN'']]|archivedate=20180513095826}}</ref> and one of the ways he prepared was by reading ''[[Star Wars: The Visual Dictionary]]''.<ref name="Bucket Head">{{SW|url=video/bucket-head|text=Bucket Head}}</ref> He was nominated for the [[2003]] [[Wikipedia:Young Artist Award|Young Actor Award]] for "Best Performance in a Feature Film - Supporting Young Actor."<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms24.htm|text=24th Annual Young Artist Awards Nominations|work=[[Wikipedia:Young Artist Award|Young Artist Award]]|archivedate=20050205074851}}</ref> Logan was originally slated by Lucas to reprise his role in [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']], with [[Lucasfilm]] holding him for a year until it was his turn to shoot his part, but his participation was ultimately written out after [[Samuel L. Jackson]] convinced Lucas to not have Logan's character return to kill Jackson's [[Mace Windu]], as Jackson felt someone powerful as his character deserved to be [[Duel in Palpatine's office|killed]] by [[Darth Sidious|someone far more threatening]] than a "punk kid."<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://www.thepopverse.com/movies-star-wars-mace-windu-death-boba-fett-daniel-logan|text=Star Wars creator George Lucas originally planned for Boba Fett to kill Mace Windu (and here's how & why Samuel L Jackson fought it)|author=Joshua Lapin-Berton|date=2025-02-24|work=[https://www.thepopverse.com Popverse]|archivedate=20250219161344}}</ref> Logan later reprised his role as Boba Fett in several episodes of ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]''.<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/movies/news/2010-03-25-empirestrikes25_CV_N.htm|text=30 years after 'Empire,' Boba Fett strikes back in a big way|author=Anthony Breznican|date=2010-03-25|work=[[Wikipedia:USA Today|''USA Today'']]|archivedate=20190807163538}}</ref> He was rumored to play a part in the unproduced [[Star Wars: Underworld|''Star Wars'' live-action TV series]].<ref>[[Star Wars Insider 99|''Star Wars Insider'' 99]]</ref><ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.theforce.net/latestnews/story/Rick_McCallum_Talks_Star_Wars_On_TV_109774.asp|text=Rick McCallum Talks ''Star Wars'' On TV|author=Mike Barrick|date=2007-11-08|work=[[TheForce.net]]|archivedate=20160422110230}}</ref>

Logan appeared in the ''[[Star Wars]]'' documentaries ''Bucket Head'',<ref name="Bucket Head" /> ''[[From Puppets to Pixels]]'' and [[W:c:starwarsfans:Heart of an Empire|''Heart of an Empire'']]. He had a blog at [[StarWars.com]],<ref>{{Blog|listing=true|daniellogan|Daniel Logan Blog|Daniel Logan}}</ref> and has appeared at multiple ''Star Wars'' conventions and reported from ''Star Wars'' events.<ref>{{SWArchive|url=kids/explore/events/f20020416/indexp5.html|text=Celebration II Report}}</ref><ref>{{OfficialBlog|url=2008/03/23/happy-easter-from-jedi-con|text=Happy Easter from Jedi-Con}}</ref><ref>{{OfficialBlog|url=2008/05/27/daniel-logan-to-blog-from-star-wars-weekends|text=Daniel Logan Reports in from Jedi-Con}}</ref><ref>{{SWArchive|url=community/event/disney/news20080410.html|text=Disney ''Star Wars'' Weekends 2008 Guest List}}</ref>

